quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  27,1,Those are the signs of the Qur'an and the perspicuous Book
  27,2,a guidance and glad tidings to the believers
  27,3,"who are steadfast at prayer, and give alms, and of the hereafter are sure"
  27,4,"verily, those who believe not in the hereafter we have made seemly for them their works, and they shall wander blindly on"
  27,5,"These are they who shall have an evil torment, and they in the hereafter shall be those who most lose"
  27,6,"Verily, thou dost meet with this Qur'an from the wise, the knowing One"
  27,7,"When Moses said to his people, 'Verily, I perceive a fire, I will bring you therefrom news; or I will bring you a burning brand; haply ye may be warned"
  27,8,"But when he came to it he was called to, 'Blessed be He who is in the fire, and he who is about it! and celebrated be the praises of God, the Lord of the Worlds"
  27,9,"O Moses! verily, I am God, the mighty, wise"
  27,10,"throw down thy staff!' and when he saw it quivering, as though it were a snake, he turned back fleeing, and did not return. 'O Moses! fear not; verily, as for me - apostles fear not with me"
  27,11,"save only those who have done wrong and then substitute good for evil; for, verily, I am forgiving, merciful"
  27,12,"but put thy hand in thy bosom, it shall come forth white without hurt;- one of nine signs to Pharaoh and his people; verily, they are a people who act abominably"
  27,13,"And when our signs came to them visibly, they said, 'This is obvious sorcery"
  27,14,"and they gainsaid them - though their souls made sure of them - unjustly, haughtily; but, behold what was the end of the evildoers"
  27,15,"And we gave David and Solomon knowledge; and they both said, 'Praise belongs to God, who hath preferred us over many of His servants who believe"
  27,16,"And Solomon was David's heir; and said, 'O ye folk! we have been taught the speech of birds, and we have been given everything; verily, this is an obvious grace"
  27,17,"And assembled for Solomon were his hosts of the ginns, and men, and birds, and they were marshalled"
  27,18,"until they came upon the valley of the ants. Said an ant, 'O ye ants! go into your dwellings, that Solomon and his hosts crush you not while they do not perceive"
  27,19,"And he smiled, laughing at her speech, and said, 'O Lord! excite me to be thankful for Thy favour, wherewith Thou hast favoured me and my parents, and to do righteousness which may please Thee; and make me enter into Thy mercy amongst Thy righteous servants"
  27,20,"And he reviewed the birds, and said, 'How is it I see not the hoopoe? is he then amongst the absent"
  27,21,I will surely torment him with a severe torment; or I will surely slaughter him; or he shall bring me obvious authority
  27,22,"And he tarried not long, and said, 'I have compassed what ye compassed not; for I bring you from Seba a sure information"
  27,23,"verily, I found a woman ruling over them, and she was given all things, and she had a mighty throne"
  27,24,"and I found her and her people adoring the sun instead of God, for Satan had made seemly to them their works, and turned them from the path, so that they are not guided"
  27,25,"Will they not adore God who brings forth the secrets in the heavens, and knows what they hide and what they manifest"
  27,26,"God, there is no god but He, the Lord of the mighty throne"